Author: friend_witha_401K
Text: This sounds like an eating disorder talking. I am in recovery from anorexia, and I know from personal experience that I didn't starve myself because I hated it. I did it because I felt a high when I stepped on the scale and saw that the number went down. And at the same time I felt hungry and light-headed and weak.   PLEASE GET HELP ASAP  [https://www.nationaleatingdisorders.org/](https://www.nationaleatingdisorders.org/)
